@node intro "Introduction"

 What is it for?

       Fast and small CLI-filelister for Dialog.
       Mainly for make AmigaGuide lists.
	
        o Replacement for old SkyList program.
        o Possibility to build AmigaGuide filelist.
        o Fast sort routines.
        o Set buffer size.
        o IBM-linefeeds ON/OFF.
        o Description length (default 40).
        o Forget area(s) where freq is not allowed.
        o List only x day(s) old files.
        o Select areas to skip.
        o Help with ?.

@endnode

@node requires "Requirements"

        o Any kind of Amiga.
        o OS 2.04 or better.
        o Dialog and Dlg.library.

@endnode

@node using "Using"
	
	DiaGFlist [-a] [-b] [-c] [-f] [-l] [-n] [-r]areas [-s] filename

	-a = Build Amigaguide list.
        -b = Buffer size = max files in one area (default 1500).
        -c = Description length (default 40).
 	-f = Do not list areas where freq is not allowed.
        -l = Add linefeed (for MS-DOS systems).
	     Not add linefeed to AGuide headers.
	-n = List x day(s) old files.
        -r = Area number(s) to skip.
        -s = Sort: 1-Date(N)/2-Date(O)/3-Size(B)/4-Size(S)/5-Name(Z-A)

        Default sort routine is filename (A-Z).

	Examples: DiaGList -a -c50 -n3 -r1-20 Ram:NewFilesA.Txt
		  DiaGList -n3 -b2000 Ram:NewFiles.Txt
		  DiaGList Ram:AllFiles.Txt
                  DiaGList -c30 -f -l -r100,200,300-400 -s1 Ram:ListNew.Txt
	
        Note !!!

        It is not anymore to necessary to mind gaps.
        If you have over 1500 files in one area, give bigger
        value to buffer. One unit (1) takes 106 bytes memory.

@endnode

